---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Button from '../components/atoms/Button.astro';
import Hero from '../components/organisms/Hero.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/organisms/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Manifesto — HPS AI Hub"
  description="How one architect builds software in 2026. AI is a tool. You are the architect."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="main">

    <Hero eyebrow="Manifesto" eyebrowIcon="lucide:lightbulb">
      <Fragment slot="title">
        AI is a tool. <span class="accent">You are the architect</span>.
      </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="lede">
        This is not a framework. This is not a product. This is how
        one architect builds software in 2026.
      </Fragment>
    </Hero>

    <!-- ── §1 What This Is ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">What This Is</h2>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          The HPS AI OS is an operating system for AI-assisted development.
          It is a set of opinions — hardened by 15 years of building real systems —
          about how a solo developer should work with AI agents.
          Not alongside them. Not under them.
          <strong>Directing them.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── §2 The Problem ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">The Problem</h2>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          Every week, a new "AI coding assistant" promises to replace developers.
          Every week, developers who never learned architecture let AI generate
          spaghetti code at the speed of light. The result is the same mess we had
          before — just produced faster.
        </p>

        <div class="callout callout-warning" data-animate="fade-up">
          <strong>Here is the thing:</strong> speed without direction is just chaos with a deadline.
        </div>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          A solo developer building proptech, IoT, cybersecurity — real systems
          with real users — cannot afford to babysit a chatbot. But they also
          cannot afford to hand over architectural decisions to a model that has
          no skin in the game. The model does not maintain your code at 3am
          when production breaks. <strong>You do.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── §3 The Philosophy ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">The Philosophy</h2>

        <p class="hero-lede" data-animate="fade-up">
          <strong>AI is a tool. You are the architect.</strong>
        </p>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          An architect does not lay every brick. But an architect decides WHERE
          every brick goes, WHY it goes there, and WHAT the building should look
          like when it is done. The bricklayers execute. In this system,
          19 named AI agents are the bricklayers.
        </p>

        <div class="principles-grid">

          <div class="principle-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <span class="principle-label">01</span>
            <h3 class="principle-title">Concepts before code</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              If you do not understand what you are building, no amount of
              AI-generated code will save you. We do not skip fundamentals.
              We do not take shortcuts. Real learning takes effort and time,
              and there is no prompt that replaces understanding.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="principle-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <span class="principle-label">02</span>
            <h3 class="principle-title">Specifications before implementation</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              Every meaningful change goes through SDD — Spec-Driven Development.
              Explore, propose, specify, design, task, implement, verify, archive.
              Nine phases. Because "just make it work" is how you build systems
              that break at scale.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="principle-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <span class="principle-label">03</span>
            <h3 class="principle-title">Memory over repetition</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              The system remembers. Decisions, conventions, gotchas, bugs —
              all persisted in Engram. An agent that forgets what it learned
              yesterday is not an agent. It is a stateless function with
              delusions of continuity. We fix that.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="principle-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <span class="principle-label">04</span>
            <h3 class="principle-title">Orchestration over configuration</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              You should describe WHAT you want, not WHO should do it.
              IntentGate classifies. The category router picks the right model.
              The worker executes. You review. That is the loop.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="principle-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <span class="principle-label">05</span>
            <h3 class="principle-title">Cost discipline</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              Not every task deserves Opus. Routine work goes to Haiku.
              Architecture goes to Opus. The system decides, not your
              wallet's anxiety.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── §4 What It Means to Be an AI Orchestrator ────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">What It Means to Be an AI Orchestrator</h2>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          It means you are the one person in the room who understands the entire
          system. You know why the database schema looks the way it does. You
          know why the API contract has that specific shape. You know why the
          frontend state is managed that particular way.
        </p>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          The AI agents know none of this. They are brilliant at the task in
          front of them and blind to everything else. <strong>YOUR job is to be
          the connective tissue</strong> — the one who sees the whole building,
          not just the current brick.
        </p>

        <h3 class="subsection-title" data-animate="fade-up">An AI orchestrator:</h3>

        <ul class="conviction-list">
          <li data-animate="fade-up">
            Writes specs, not code, as their primary output
          </li>
          <li data-animate="fade-up">
            Reviews AI work with the same rigor they would apply to a junior developer
          </li>
          <li data-animate="fade-up">
            Saves every decision to memory because context is the most expensive thing in this system
          </li>
          <li data-animate="fade-up">
            Never trusts AI output without verification — not because AI is bad, but because trust without verification is not engineering
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── §5 The Conviction ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section conviction-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">The Conviction</h2>

        <p class="prose" data-animate="fade-up">
          I built this because I was tired of the false choice: either you code
          everything yourself, or you let AI drive and hope for the best.
          There is a third way. You architect. You specify. You orchestrate.
          And you hold the entire system accountable to YOUR standards.
        </p>

        <div class="conviction-pullquote" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p class="pullquote-line">One developer.</p>
          <p class="pullquote-line">Nineteen agents.</p>
          <p class="pullquote-line">Zero excuses.</p>
          <p class="pullquote-emphasis">The human always leads.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="signature" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p class="sig-name">Hamilton Posada</p>
          <p class="sig-meta">Architect · GDE · MVP</p>
          <p class="sig-meta">Building between Spain and the Netherlands</p>
          <p class="sig-meta">2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection
      title="Read how the manifesto turns into architecture."
      lede="From philosophy to 9 layers, 20 agents, 66 skills — the whole thing is public and reproducible."
    >
      <Fragment slot="cta">
        <Button href="/architecture" variant="primary" icon="lucide:arrow-right" iconPosition="end">Architecture</Button>
        <Button href="/agents" variant="ghost" icon="lucide:bot">Agent Roster</Button>
      </Fragment>
    </CTASection>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .main {
    min-height: calc(100vh - 80px);
  }

  /* ── Content Sections ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .content-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-10);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .section-inner {
    max-width: var(--container-max);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: var(--space-6);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .subsection-title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── Callout ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .callout {
    padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-block: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 65ch;
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .callout-warning {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }

  .callout strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* ── Principles Grid ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .principles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .principles-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .principle-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    position: relative;
  }

  .principle-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .principle-title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .principle-desc {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* ── Conviction List ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .conviction-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-5) 0 0 0;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .conviction-list li {
    padding: var(--space-4) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text);
    position: relative;
  }

  .conviction-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .conviction-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* ── Conviction Section (the closer) ──────────────────────────── */
  .conviction-pullquote {
    margin-block: var(--space-10);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .pullquote-line {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .pullquote-emphasis {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  /* ── Signature ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .signature {
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .sig-name {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .sig-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
</style>
